BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Montclair State University
CATEGORIES:Arts
CATEGORIES:Cultural
CATEGORIES:Small Scale
CATEGORIES:Drop By
CATEGORIES:Casual/ Relaxed
DESCRIPTION:The Department of Art & Design invites you to From the Basemen
 t\, the BFA Visual Communications Design 2026 Graduate Exhibition. Join u
 s at the Finley Gallery from March 25 to April 7 to experience a dynamic 
 showcase of work by graduating VCDS students\, featuring posters\, motion
  graphics\, packaging\, editorial\, and more. With the opening reception 
 on Friday\, March 27\, 4 to 6pm.\n \nVenture into the world of graphic de
 sign at the VCDS 2026 graduate exhibition\, From the Basement. This exhib
 ition highlights the work of graduating Visual Communication Design stude
 nts and the projects they developed throughout their time in the VCDS BFA
  program. A range of mediums will be featured\, including posters\, motio
 n graphics\, packaging\, editorial\, and more! Together\, these works ref
 lect the unique styles and creative voices of the class.\n \nFeatured Des
 igners:\nJalen Aguirre\, Ysabella De Leon\, Brett Diese\, Domenic Faliven
 e\, Anna Fronczkowski\, Tori Gallagher\, Camila Garcia\, Robert Gaskill\,
  Britany Giraldo\, David Guerra\, Audrey Hitchens\, Natalia Kurpiewski\, 
 Paolo La Rosa\, Izzy Latella\, Katie Mascuch\, Caitlin Mendoza\, Evan Oku
 n\, Erika Oliva\, Julia Oliveri\, Christian Pajaro\, Nicole Ricci\, Chris
 topher Rizzi\, Casey Ryu\, Tom Sheridan\, Michael Shimabukuro\, Gabby Tre
 zza\, Maral Tutunjian\, and Dogan Uludogan\n \nBFA Visual Communications 
 Design Graduate Exhibition\nExhibition dates: March 25–April 7\, 2026\nOp
 ening Reception: Friday\, March 27\, 4–6pm\nFinley Gallery\, Finley Hall\
 n \nCome meet the designers and celebrate their work! Support the next ge
 neration of designers as they transition from academia into the professio
 nal world.\n\nHosted by: Art and Design\n\nAdditional Information can be 
 found at: https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12352690
DTEND:20260326T230000Z
DTSTAMP:20260323T025109Z
DTSTART:20260326T150000Z
LOCATION:Finley Gallery\, Finley Hall
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:BFA Visual Communications Design Graduate Exhibition
UID:https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12352690
URL:https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12352690
X-HOSTS:Art and Design
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Montclair State University
CATEGORIES:Arts
CATEGORIES:Cultural
DESCRIPTION:With the loss of "third spaces\," an increase in online social
 ization\, and the dwindling of social clubs and groups\, we are increasin
 gly seeking a way to combat loneliness and isolation. Through their abili
 ty to bring people together in person and to connect our hearts to beat a
 s one\, the arts remain a powerful way to bring us closer to those around
  us. Donna Walker-Kuhne\, the nation's foremost expert in audience develo
 pment\, leads an inspiring discussion on how artistic communities can mea
 ningfully connect\, grow inclusive audiences\, and create a more vibrant 
 artistic world. In this open and inviting conversation\, she shares concr
 ete examples of successful audience outreach from her extensive field exp
 erience\, as well as spotlighting young Champions for the Arts in the Mon
 tclair State University community. They're ready to pledge their commitme
 nt to forging dynamic strategies to strengthen the arts. Are you ready to
  join them?\n \nDonna Walker-Kuhne is an award-winning thought leader\, l
 awyer\, scholar\, educator\, writer\, and strategist for community engage
 ment\, audience development\, and social justice. Acknowledged as the nat
 ion‘s foremost expert on audience development by the Arts & Business Coun
 cil\, she has worked with NJPAC\, Dance Theatre of Harlem\, Alvin Ailey A
 merican Dance Theater\, The Public Theater\, WNYC Radio\, The Apollo Thea
 ter\, and more\, and consulted on over 22 Broadway productions. As founde
 r and president of Walker International Communications Group\, Inc.\, she
  has raised over $23 million in earned income by promoting the arts to di
 verse communities. Walker is the author of Invitation to the Party\, Buil
 ding Bridges to Arts\, Culture\, and Community\, and Champions for the Ar
 ts\, Successful Strategies for Engaging Dynamic Communities.\n \nTickets 
 to this event are free for all\, not just students! To join us\, reserve 
 a seat online here or at the Alexander Kasser Theatre box office\, Monday
  through Friday between 12 and 6 PM.\n\nHosted by: PEAK Performances\n\nA
 dditional Information can be found at: https://montclair.campuslabs.com/e
 ngage/event/12341667
DTEND:20260326T233000Z
DTSTAMP:20260323T025109Z
DTSTART:20260326T220000Z
GEO:40.860400;-74.197600
LOCATION:Presentation Hall\, College of Media and Communication Building
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Champions for the Arts with Donna Walker-Kuhne
UID:https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12341667
URL:https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12341667
X-HOSTS:PEAK Performances
END:VEVENT
