DESCRIPTION:Coffeehouse is our live music event where students can sign up
  to perform in Russ Lounge. Whether you’re playing\, singing\, or just co
 ming to hang out\, it’s always a great night of creativity and community.
 \nThe goal of the event is to turn Russ Lounge into a performance space t
 hat can accommodate an audience\, but it’s also a hands-on opportunity to
  learn how to set up a performance from start to finish. We will be mixin
 g on a Midas M32R\, so it's also an opportunity to learn how digital mixe
 rs for live audio work. All that prep work culminates in a show featuring
  Montclair State students from 7 PM to 9:15 PM. We go through the process
  of setup\, performance\, and breakdown. IF this interests you\, please f
 ill out this form for more information on how to join the crew.\nSee you 
 soon\, stay groovy!!\nAll students are welcome\, commuters need to be sig
 ned in a with a resident following Residence Life guest registration proc
 edures.\n\nHosted by: Freeman Hall & Russ Hall\n\nAdditional Information 
 can be found at: https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12333913
DTEND:20260328T010000Z
DTSTAMP:20260323T025109Z
DTSTART:20260327T231500Z
