DESCRIPTION:THE EPIC OF ANCIENT IRELAND\nDr. Matthieu BoydProfessor of Lit
 eratureFairleigh Dickinson University\n \nDr. Matthieu Boyd will be discu
 ssing his new translation of the Irish epic "Táin Bó Cúailnge" (Broadview
  Press\, 2025)\, an important development in ancient and medieval Celtic 
 Studies and the study of myth and epic. Once touted as "a window on the I
 ron Age\," the Táin is considered an invaluable source of information on 
 Pagan and early Christian Irish society and its literature.\nWED.\, APRIL
  16:30 – 8:30 PMDICKSON HALL\, ROOM 178\n \nPlease contact Professor Glen
  Robert Gill at gillg@montclair.edufor additional details.\n \nMONTCLAIR 
 STATE UNIVERSITYClassics and General HumanitiesCollege of Humanities and 
 Social Sciences\n\nHosted by: College of Humanities and Social Sciences (
 CHSS)\n\nAdditional Information can be found at: https://montclair.campus
 labs.com/engage/event/12354064
